SIMPLE: swedenborgian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swedenborgian
<hw>Swe`den*bor"gi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who
holds the doctrines of the New Jerusalem church, as taught by Emanuel
<xex>Swedenborg</xex>, a Swedish philosopher and religious writer, who
was born <sc>a. d.</sc> 1688 and died 1772. Swedenborg claimed to have
intercourse with the spiritual world, through the opening of his
spiritual senses in 1745. He taught that the Lord Jesus Christ, as
comprehending in himself all the fullness of the Godhead, is the one
only God, and that there is a spiritual sense to the Scriptures, which
he (Swedenborg) was able to reveal, because he saw the correspondence
between natural and spiritual things.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swedenborgian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swedenborgian
<hw>Swe`den*bor"gi*an</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
Swedenborg or his views.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swedenborgianism</ent>⟦br⟧
